content: It would be a 5 but this app sucks the battery dry. Would appreciate you solving that as it's hard to play 1 game without my hands getting to hot!

Some of the hints really need a review, I'm not even sure kings #23 is possible. Hint #3 requires you to ignore the potential 1 in either r4c2 or r7c1, both of which should be 5s - however you're not able to figure that out without placing to the 1s in hint #3, so it's a solve loop
Great app and really enjoying the puzzles. Latest update has made the level selection screen painfully slow and laggy though.
No new puzzles in over three months, despite the promise of five new puzzles a month. Really disappointing. Update: after over 5 months, 15 puzzles have been added.
Great challenging puzzles and excellent gameplay

The game itself is great! The clues however are often not very helpful, as I find that I took a completely different path which has not been considered... It would also be good to have both types of pencil marks, like you have on the computer app (something to think about for the next update!).
Good puzzles. But the game updated automatically and all my progress is gone. And i have to play them over again which is annoying.

Clear, simple graphics. Easy to master controls. Best played on a tablet, for real estate. This game takes so much of the pain away it's difficult going back to paper, especially using the non-logic method I like to refer to as, "What are you .. That's not how you .. Why are you doing .. Dear God, no! Please, please just stop." To everyone involved, thank you. Knight's move puzzle 15 has kept me going for months. Thought I had it today, but, sadly not. Edit: I tried again and GOT IT!!! :D :D
The CTC sudoku apps are by far my favorites and this is no exception.

I was very happy when this came out. My favourite is knight sudoku. However recently finishing all puzzles, I was a bit upset it just came to an end. I don't know why, but I was sort of expecting to get puzzles that would mix them together, or have other rules. I recently played a puzzle online that had evens a knight moves and odds as queens. I was expecting to find somewhere to do all of those but none available sadly :(
Great puzzles that never need guessing to complete the puzzles

Saw this recommended on YouTube. I wish the YouTuber or developer would update the app with his recent ultra hard challenges. Or combine the modes for even more challenging arrangements. That being said this format has spoiled me playing soduko. I love the game modes and controls.
Tricky but in a good way. Makes you see sudokus very differently
First sudoku: 22 minutes, second sudoku: 5 minutes. Now we are cooking with gas!
Great but expensive
Well worth the price. Even after finishing every puzzle, I went back and tried and tried until I got times I was happy with. Got quite a bit of play time out of it.
The description says it updates frequently but it rarely ever does. I think I've seen 2 updates since I downloaded it in April or May.
Hours and hours of unique and challenging puzzles worth the price and love the new queen soduko addition ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐

Solid interface but a bit cramped. For example, it's difficult to hit the color button you're aiming for -- at least with my Pixel 3a XL and my thumb. The puzzles are top notch but they get harder WAY too quickly IMO, and there aren't very many. I'd love to see all these apps integrated into a single app with purchasable packs. Also, some kind of tier system so novices can practice with the easier puzzles while the experts can jump straight to the harder ones.
Real fun, but drains my battery in mere minutes. Would not recommend because of it.

Great app, lots of good hand-crafted sudoku. Ignore all the people pointing out issues with queen sudoku, they've all just misunderstood the rules, despite the fact that they're clearly explained in the app itself.
Great app for variant sudoku
Puzzles I love grinding at and learn from. So much better than machine-built puzzles. Handcrafted with handcrafted hints. Great stuff.
When you commit to a monthly update schedule, try to adhere to it.

Slightly disappointing that the very first Queen's move Sudoku is broken from the very start, not allowing an 8 anywhere in box 1. However, I have not had a problem with any Knight or Kings move puzzles. Overall I think with a little tweaking, and more puzzles in total, this app would be worth it.
Love the king and knight sudokus but the queen ones have many errors of same numbers on diagonals.
Just like the standard sudoku app (which has finally updated) the update window has come and went. Really disappointed.

If you're not here for the hints, no worries, it's a great app. The hints often are completely incorrect. Hint #3 on puzzle 16 of chess sudoku says you can place a 7 in column 4, but there's 2 possibilities for 7 in the column, in the box, and in the row. I think this also skews the difficulty on puzzles with incorrect hints, usually making them far harder than their star rating as the puzzles WOULD be easy enough if they worked the way the hints suggest.
I believe hint 2 in queen sudoku level 14 is wrong. A 9 in r4c2 would force a 9 into r3c6, not r6c3... Great app by the way.
Really enjoying this app. Nice variety of puzzles.

Got here from "Cracking the cryptic" channel. Great app. Has many quality-of-life features to guard you from being disappointed when it's getting hard. Queen sudoku needs some work, but I'll give you the credit, because the rest is great. Totally worth it!
Excellent puzzles, controls, and overall experience.

Oh wow I love this app. I am really enjoying the last update. The combination of the Chess moves with Sudoku is amazing! As I finish puzzle after puzzle I am so satisfied with the amount of logic that has washed through my brain.
Absolutely super, beautiful puzzles with tools if you got stuck.
Great app. Fun and challenging puzzle.
I love the puzzle and I even watch them on YouTube, they are really fun but I finished them all ages ago and need more puzzles. Is there any coming soon?
Tremendous challenge without being overwhelming.

Great games but massive battery sap. Should combine the apps into one with extra packs. If you don't solve them the same way as the person who set the puzzle thinks you will, then the hints can be quite useless. They assume you've already got to a certain point and are stuck there.
Really good app. The UI is smooth and the puzzles are entertaining to solve.
Its a great little app for sudoku. But the new Queen game mode doesn't quite work. It doesn't follow the restraints set out, and there ends up being repeated digits along diagonals
So apparently I can't read. So I would like to take back everything I said. I did not realize that it was only 9s that operate as queens.
Fantastic app!

This might seem nitpicky, and I apologize for such, but the "highlight restricted cells" doesn't work for the queen sudoku puzzles, and the handy "?" button in the corner of the queen sudoku puzzle also only displays the rules of classic sudoku. I know you guys have been swamped, so this may be a simple error, but I figured you should know.
Poor value compared to the sandwich variant. Love the app and puzzles but am slightly dissapointed this hasn't received any new updates for some time.
These are handcrafted games, which means the logic and the presentation are beautiful and elegant. I highly recommend them!
Fantastic game. Best sudoku interface I've found so far, as well. Can't wait for more puzzles to come out!
Awesome game, but no new puzzles for almost 2 months now... Too bad...
Absolutely loved it. Can't wait for more to come

I love this app! I've always loved sudoku and particularly enjoyed the gradual increase in difficulty that meant I didn't feel like I would fail the "latest" puzzle because it was impossible based on my skill/logic. I'm eagerly awaiting the Queen sudoku puzzles and anymore King or Knight puzzles if there are any - so far I think Knight is my favourite.
Really fun puzzles try to switch between the 2 types
AmaZing stuff
Amazing! I love chess sudoku, it's probably my favorite variant.
Perfect
Fantastic
Fantastic, approachable puzzles with lovely logic and useful hints if you get stuck! Love the channel, love the app guys!
Great puzzles and nice interface as well!
Great way to learn chess sudoku, some really excellent puzzles and interesting logic!

Great game, but the hints leave something to be desired. Some describe a location that is outright incorrect, and some seem half written compared to others. Also some hints require you to have certain numbers already placed, in which case if you haven't solved it in the order that CTC has, the hint makes no sense for you
Fantastic
Great chess sudoku app. Wonderful YouTube channel.
If you like Sudoku but are looking for something a bit different, you'll love this.
Awesome puzzle game, check out cracking the crypt YouTube channel. If you like what you see their then you will love this 🤠 Money well spent in my opinion 👌👍

Stunning, absolutely genious. Just finished the last King Puzzle and my oh my I feel so clever for having made it on my own! Thank you, Simon and Mark! Can't wait for the next set! Well worth the money.
Its good, but definitely not enough puzzles, and no queen sudoku variants yet :(

Overall an enjoyable game but definitely not enough puzzles (45 in total) to justify the $5 price point. I expect that as level count increases. I do enjoy the controls and see a no problem with the row layout for numbers. Can't wait for more puzzles.

I love the new twist of adding certain chess rules into the sudoku mix, which adds a fresh new take to a classic puzzle. The hints do an excellent job of walking you through the logic as it's meant to be solved, rather than revealing the answer straight away, and the two notation styles let me keep better track of my progress. Overall, this app contains a well-crafted set of chess sudoku puzzles!

This takes Sudoku to a new level. Added restrictions based on chess movements fits so well into Sudoku. The functions really well, and I'm glad it has various options in the settings to help make the game more challenging. I'm anxiously awaiting the addition of Queen Sudoku levels. I'll definitely be purchasing the Sandwich Sudoku app as well (and would love to see a Thermo Sudoku app in the future too)

World class, hand crafted puzzles. Currently only 45 puzzles makes the asking price a bit steep but the quality of these puzzles are worth the money. I feel that I have learnt a lot from playing this app, much more than I would solving a computer generated puzzle.

The app is simple and well designed. The controls are easy to use. Hints are well written. There are only 40 puzzles total. 20 Knight and 20 King in increasing difficulty. I played through all the puzzles in three days and the app has no gameplay left.

The puzzles are awesome, I like the new dimension the system adds. And I like it a lot that even the easier puzzles are something you need to actually engange your brain for, so you won't get bored before unlocking the more difficult ones. However I too would prefer the numbers to be in a 3x3 pad instead of a row with tiny buttons, and then the tools could go in a 3x3 pad besides that. If that could be added this app will immediately deserve a 5th star!
Genius puzzles. Really nice and different from normal sudokus. A whole new way of solving sudokus. There are also clear instructions for if you are new to chess sudokus. Would recommend!
Very much looking forward to queen sudoku being added, as well as more puzzles in the other variants. Take your time pushing those out, stay healthy!
Get ready to be let on an amazing journey of thought.
As good as the other two

The app is wonderful, with all the controls I've come to appreciate from Cracking the Cryptic YouTube. Knights sudoku is all kinds of fun with the given logic constraints. Kings Sudoku, however, feels poorly constructed. Those puzzles either barely use the unique constraint at all, or feel like they are deliberately set to avoid the constraint entirely, leaving us with bog-standard ordinary sudoku games, which is not what this app was supposed to be about.
Fantastic puzzles!

Waited until I got through all the puzzles before writing this. The knight varient is a real brain teaser, needing to think in ways you don't normally do in order to get those tricky insights to clear them. The kings varient felt more like a slow march to completion. The only times I got stuck there was when I discarded an option in my mind but kept the notation.
Challenging puzzles, good interface. 5/5
Nice app for sudoku variants. One flaw: it does not show the type (rules) while playing.

Love the game. The interface is quite similar to their earlier games. I like it that every puzzle is hand designed and the hints are just brilliant. Most computer generated sudoku would give hints as a number on the grid (which is simply terrible because you really dont learn anything from it) but this game, in line with their earlier games, give hints that make you think about certain parts of the grid and derive the solution path yourself. Just excellent!
Another excellent set of handcrafted Sudoku puzzles from the Cracking the Cryptic team. The App interface is a joy to use.

Another great app from the Cracking the Cryptic Crew! Fantastic puzzle that are challenging and fun to do. As with the Classic Sudoku app though there are two things that would make it perfect: 1) The option to add your own puzzles 2) Darker themes or dark mode compatibility with the system theme Add those two and it's 5 stars all the way!
Really great puzzles, especially the knight ones. Really looking forward to the Queen puzzles. Keep these apps coming boys they're phenomenal in terms of quality compared to all then other apps.
Another amazing Sudoku app varient from these amazing guys with all the custumization options you need, much love from South Africa.
Love the interface and variations of puzzle rather than your standard Sudoku!
A really fun variant sudoku app!

After watching dozens of CrackingTheCryptic videos I got the Classic Sudoku app and have really been enjoy it. I was excited for this variant (three really!) because of the extra spacial aspect to it and let me say I haven't been disappointed! The puzzles are really a joy to solve and I find them to be a bit easier than the Classic puzzles which really helps my ego 😂
A fun variant of the best sudoku app on the market

Edit: OMG I didnt see the settings to turn off highlighting. Thanks for the response, keep making these apps and I'll keep buying them. <3 Love the handcrafted puzzles created for this app, thanks for the hard work Mark and Simon.
replyContent:
Hi Bradley, 

You can disable the highlights by setting "Highlight Restricted Cells" to off in the Gameplay Settings menu. Also, you might want to try out the "Tool" Control Method, it might be more in line with what you're looking for. 

Cheers,
Nick

content: No frills gameplay, easy to understand rules, and excellent puzzles. I love the extra challenge and the ability to edit how the game can assist me with errors.
Great interface with awesome handcrafted puzzles
Yet another stonking sudoku app from Cracking the Cryptic. Love it!
